2. **Star Characteristics**: The host star of Planet_1 has twice the mass of the host star of Planet_2, but both stars have the same radii. The mass of the star affects the gravitational pull and the orbital speed of the planet, but since the radii are the same, the geometric probability of transit is primarily influenced by the orbital period.

